Inside Macintosh: Cyberdog Programmer's Kit / Part 3 - Cyberdog Reference
Chapter 7 - Classes and Methods / CyberSession

GetCyberDraft

Retrieves the draft of the Cyberdog session document.

ODDraft GetCyberDraft ();
return value
An ODDraft that represents the session document draft.
DISCUSSION
You call this method to retrieve the draft of the Cyberdog session document. If the draft does not exist, this method creates one. To determine whether a display part is contained in the Cyberdog session document, you should call IsInCyberDraft.

Do not subclass this class.

SEE ALSO
The IsInCyberDraft method (page 367).
